From 25a429ac657324feb640f2484b1036979bd4a9e8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: KITOHSY <hongsun900912@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 17:21:54 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] T14: add ScBrokerClient for Broker pairing relay
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SmartClassroom T14 — a small QObject that POSTs {connect-token, PIN} to the
SmartClassroom Broker (POST <brokerUrl>/api/v1/pairing) so the Broker can
relay the PIN to the host's Sunshine /api/pin endpoint (task T08). This is
what lets headless pairing complete without the user typing a PIN.

  * NvHTTP is GameStream-only and GET-only, so it cannot be reused for an
    outbound JSON POST. ScBrokerClient uses QNetworkAccessManager +
    QJsonDocument (the autoupdatechecker.cpp pattern).

  * Asynchronous: requestPairing() returns immediately and pairingRelayed()
    is emitted on the owning thread once the Broker responds — success on
    HTTP 200 + {"status":"paired_pending"}, failure otherwise with a short
    machine-readable reason (bad_broker_url / broker_unreachable /
    http_<code> / the Broker's own error code).

  * 15s transfer timeout — generous enough for the Broker's exponential
    backoff when relaying to Sunshine.

  * app.pro gains the new source/header.
